 Sergio Aguero marked his 350th Man City game with two goals as they beat Southampton 3-1 to reach the Carabao Cup quarter-finals. After fellow Argentina international Nicolas Otamendi headed City in front in the 20th minute, Aguero struck in either half to move on to 12 goals for the season. ALSO READ: How Nigerian forward Osimhen adapted to life in Lille Despite Jack Stephens’ late consolation goal, it was a pretty routine win against a Southampton side still reeling from Friday’s 9-0 home defeat to Leicester, but one City fans will remember as a famous name from their past emerged as the next youngster hoping to be part of the future. Continue reading Aguero steers Man City through to Carabao Cup quarter-finals at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard